, \"from\": 716, \"to\": 738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith was the star of the show, and while she did not win gold in her favoured 200m breaststroke event, sheheld on for silverafter producing a superb performance to win gold in the 100m breaststroke.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 940, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Smith\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 746}, {\"ngram\": \"the star\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 759}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 771}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 803}, {\"ngram\": \"200m breaststroke event\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 843}, {\"ngram\": \"silverafter\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 871}, {\"ngram\": \"a superb performance\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 902}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 914}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having made history as South Africa's most decorated Olympian with four career medals (two gold and two silver), Smith announced her retirement at her peak.\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 965, \"end\": 977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999958518692071, \"rank\": 4.06315009769747e-06, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 995, \"end\": 1003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999805140762, \"rank\": 1.9485845568878488e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"four career medals\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1027}, {\"ngram\": \"two gold\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"two silver\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1052}, {\"ngram\": \"Smith\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"her retirement\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"her peak\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the track, after missing out by 0.01 in the men's 100m final, there was relief for consistent sprinter Akani Simbine as heearned an elusive Olympic medal, anchoring a young 4x100m relay squad to silver and a new national record (37.57 seconds).\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1112}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's 100m\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"relief\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1181}, {\"ngram\": \"an elusive Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1256}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"37.57 seconds\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1345}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hatherly was equally impressive in the men's mountain bike cross country race,digging deep to claim bronzeafter a hard-fought contest.\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1483, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the men's mountain bike cross country race\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"a hard-fought contest\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1482}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the Blitzboks produced a stunning result.\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Blitzboks\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"a stunning result\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1529}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After struggling to qualify for the showpiece, they beat Australia in thebronze medal playoffof the men's rugby sevens tournament.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1588, \"end\": 1597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999472368568114, \"rank\": 2.921758514596707e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the showpiece\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1576}, {\"ngram\": \"thebronze medal playoffof\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1626}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's rugby\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1642}, {\"ngram\": \"sevens tournament\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1660}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Van Dyk's result was also a surprise.\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Van Dyk's result\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1679}, {\"ngram\": \"a surprise\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After setting a personal best of 64.22m in the qualifying round, shelaunched a 63.93m throwin the women's javelin final to grab silver.\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"64.22m\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1740}, {\"ngram\": \"the qualifying round\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"a 63.93m\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was some disappointment too, with a few medal contenders missing out, including Pieter Coetze in the swimming pool and the national men's 4x400m relay team on the track.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 2013, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some disappointment\", \"from\": 1848, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"a few medal contenders\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1900}, {\"ngram\": \"Pieter Coetze\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1937}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming pool\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1958}, {\"ngram\": \"the national men's 4x400m relay team\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1999}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2012}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even in those events, however, national records were broken along the way.\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2088, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those events\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2034}, {\"ngram\": \"national records\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2061}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 2080, \"to\": 2087}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coetze finished fifth and seventh in the 100m (52.58) and 200m (1:55.60) backstroke finals respectively, but he broke the African records in both events, while the 4x400m relay team (Gardeo Isaacs, Zakithi Nene, Lythe Pillay and Antonie Matthys Nortje) also set a new SA mark of 2:58.12 to finish fifth in their final.\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2296, \"end\": 2300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\", \"score\": 0.9998399397848944, \"rank\": 0.00016008583868613258, \"text\": \"Nene\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\"}, {\"begin\": 2327, \"end\": 2334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Matthys\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthys\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Matthys\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Matthys\"}, {\"begin\": 2358, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.428519636165129e-17, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Coetze\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2096}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100m\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2135}, {\"ngram\": \"200m\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2152}, {\"ngram\": \"1:55.60) backstroke finals\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2180}, {\"ngram\": \"the African records\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2227}, {\"ngram\": \"both events\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2242}, {\"ngram\": \"the 4x400m relay team\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2271}, {\"ngram\": \"(Gardeo Isaacs\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2286}, {\"ngram\": \"Lythe Pillay\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2314}, {\"ngram\": \"2:58.12\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2376}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All-in-all, the national team's performance in the French capital was as good as could have been expected, and it was a significant improvement on the all-round effort at the Tokyo Olympics in 2021 where the SA squad earned only three medals.\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6351948138581238, \"rank\": 0.3163747613278884, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2618, \"end\": 2620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.428519636165129e-17, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the national team's performance\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2453}, {\"ngram\": \"a significant improvement\", \"from\": 2528, \"to\": 2553}, {\"ngram\": \"the all-round effort\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2577}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2599}, {\"ngram\": \"only three medals\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2651}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And with multiple rising stars sticking up their hands with impressive results in various sports, the future looks bright.\", \"from\": 2654, \"to\": 2776, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"multiple rising stars\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2684}, {\"ngram\": \"their hands\", \"from\": 2697, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"impressive results\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2732}, {\"n